Rating: 3
Some people complained about the grittiness of the cornmeal in this recipe. This can happen in any corn muffin recipe. There are two solutions: use a fine corn meal, or corn flour, instead of the rougher grind most of us have in our pantries. Try health food stores for fine-ground cornmeal/flour. The other trick is to stir together the milk and cornmeal and let that soak for half an hour before mixing in all the other ingredients. This yields a soft, cornbread-type texture, with pleasant contrasting textures. Using corn flour will yield a more cake-like muffin. Both are good!

