Rating: 3
Ok, I really liked the idea of making this into a savory versus sweet option. Here's what I tried, it's probably a new item, but it was based here so I thought I'd include it here. Cut the corn meal in half and replace it with flour. Keep the honey but replace the sugar with freshly grated cheese (I used a mix of asiago and romano). I included two teaspoons each of freshly minced basil and rosemary. Add a teaspoon of olive oil to keep the muffins moist since you're not adding fruit. Baking time stays the same but you end up with 10 muffins instead of 12 due to the missing two cups of fruit. It was very well received. Let me know your thoughts!

