Rating: 3
I agree with previous reviewers -- this is an extremely moist muffin. So much so that I had to let them completely cool in the tins before being able to remove them in one piece. I find most muffin recipes not sweet enough, so I normally increase the amount of sugar. But not this one! It was great, as is, with a pronounced honey flavor. Personally, I thought that worked well with the corn taste, but if you're not a big fan of honey, you might not like that. Knowing now how much the honey flavor comes through, I would definitely try different kinds of honey. I did not have any fresh blueberries, so I used a 16 oz bag of frozen blueberries (which came to a little over 2 cups) instead. I did not thaw or rinse them, but I did make sure any clumps were broken up. There were plenty of berries (which I liked!), but I actually ended up with 13 muffins. One problem I encountered was that the edges of the muffins burned slightly at 425, even before the tester came out clean. I tried it at 400, but there was no difference. Maybe next time I shall divide them into 14 muffins, and lower the temp to 375. Did anyone else have this problem?

